ndation for an Azure Kinect to\n75: ComfyUI pose/depth bridge. Live device capture is out of scope until explicitly\n76: approved after hardware connectivity is available.\n77: \n78: ## Non-negotiable safety rules\n79: 1. Work only inside this repository and the assigned Git worktree.\n80: 2. Never access /mnt/f, other project directories, user home data, secrets,\n81:    model directories, ComfyUI installations, or hardware devices unless a task\n82:    explicitly grants access and a human approval token exists.\n83: 3. Never run sudo, package-manager installs, driver/firmware actions, service\n84:    changes, network publishing, git push, git merge, git reset --hard, or\n85:    destructive deletion.\n86: 4. Never edit AGENTS.md, opencode.json, .opencode/, contracts/, scripts/policy*,\n87:    or orchestrator policy files unless the task explicitly owns that path and a\n88:    human approval token is present.\n89: 5. One worker owns one worktree and one declared path scope. Do not modify files\n90:    outside owned_paths. Do not inspect other worker worktrees.\n91: 6. Do not change shared interfaces opportunistically. Emit\n92:    BLOCKED_INTERFACE_CHANGE with options and a recommendation.\n93: 7. Use synthetic fixtures only. Do not claim hardware, depth alignment, body\n94:    tracking, or FLUX/Klein behavior was tested without an artifact proving it.\n95: 8. Make small atomic changes. Run only task-approved tests. Report the exact\n96:    commit SHA and structured status before declaring a task complete.\n97: 9. Never fabricate test results, SDK behavior, model availability, or source\n98:    citations. State uncertainty and request an approval or research task.\n99: \n100: ## Required worker result\n101: Every worker completion must include:\n102: - task_id and status: completed | blocked | needs_approval | failed\n103: - scope actually changed\n104: - files_changed\n105: - tests run and exact results\n106: - commit SHA\n107: - known risks and next action\n108: EOF\n109: \n110: cat > opencode.json <<'EOF'\n111: {\n112:   \"$schema\": \"https://opencode.ai/config.json\",\n113:   \"share\": \"disabled\",\n114:   \"autoupdate\": \"notify\",\n115:   \"default_agent\": \"orchestrator\",\n116:   \"instructions\": [\"AGENTS.md\"],\n117:   \"watcher\": {\n118:     \"ignore\": [\n119:       \".git/**\",\n120:       \".venv/**\",\n121:       \"state/**\",\n122:       \"worktrees/**\",\n123:       \"models/**\",\n124:       \"output/**\"\n125:     ]\n126:   },\n127:   \"permission\": {\n128:     \"external_directory\": \"deny\",\n129:     \"webfetch\": \"ask\",\n130:     \"websearch\": \"ask\",\n131:     \"question\": \"allow\",\n132:     \"doom_loop\": \"ask\",\n133:     \"task\": \"deny\",\n134:     \"bash\": {\n135:       \"*\": \"ask\"\n136:     },\n137:     \"edit\": {\n138:       \"*\": \"ask\"\n139:     }\n140:   },\n141:   \"agent\": {\n142:     \"orchestrator\": {\n143:       \"description\": \"Read-only project planner and dispatcher. It never edits, merges, installs, or deploys.\",\n144:       \"mode\": \"primary\",\n145:       \"model\": \"REPLACE_WITH_STRONG_REASONING_MODEL\",\n146:       \"temperature\": 0.1,\n147:       \"maxSteps\": 12,\n148:       \"prompt\": \".opencode/agents/orchestrator.md\",\n149:       \"permission\": {\n150:         \"read\": \"allow\",\n151:         \"glob\": \"allow\",\n152:         \"grep\": \"allow\",\n153:         \"list\": \"allow\",\n154:         \"edit\": \"deny\",\n155:         \"bash\": {\n156:           \"*\": \"deny\",\n157:           \"git status*\": \"allow\",\n158:           \"git log*\": \"allow\",\n159:           \"git diff*\": \"allow\"\n160:         },\n161:         \"task\": {\n162:           \"capture-worker\": \"allow\",\n163:           \"pose-worker\": \"allow\",\n164:           \"comfy-worker\": \"allow\",\n165:           \"reviewer\": \"allow\"\n166:         }\n167:       }\n168:     }\n169:   }\n170: }\n171: EOF\n172: \n173: cat > .opencode/agents/orchestrator.md <<'EOF'\n174: ---\n175: description: Read-only orchestrator for the Azure Kinect ComfyUI project\n176: mode: primary\n177: hidden: false\n178: ---\n179: \n180: You are the orchestrator. You plan, delegate, inspect worker reports, and request\n181: human decisions. You NEVER edit files, run package installations, merge branches,\n182: push Git, deploy, access hardware, or override policy.\n183: \n184: Before delegating:\n185: 1. Read AGENTS.md and contracts/task.schema.json.\n186: 2. Ensure every task has one owner, explicit owned_paths, acceptance criteria,\n187:    test commands, maximum attempts, and an approval requirement if applicable.\n188: 3. Prefer parallel tasks only when owned_paths do not overlap.\n189: 4. Give each worker only the minimum relevant context.\n190: 5. If an interface or policy change is needed, create a needs_approval request.\n191: \n192: Worker retry policy:\n193: - One routine repair attempt is allowed for a deterministic test/lint failure.\n194: - After two failed attempts, stop and request human review.\n195: - Never silently upgrade a model, expand scope, grant permissions, install\n196:   dependencies, or modify shared contracts.\n197: EOF\n198: \n199: cat > .opencode/agents/capture-worker.md <<'EOF'\n200: ---\n201: description: Builds mocked Azure Kinect frame-source abstractions only\n202: mode: subagent\n203: hidden: true\n204: temperature: 0.2\n205: maxSteps: 18\n206: permission:\n207:   external_directory: deny\n208:   task: deny\n209:   webfetch: ask\n210:   websearch: ask\n211:   bash:\n212:     \"*\": deny\n213:     \"git status*\": allow\n214:     \"git diff*\": allow\n215:     \"git add src/azure_kinect_comfyui/capture/* tests/capture/* fixtures/*\": allow\n216:     \"git commit -m *\": ask\n217:     \"python -m pytest tests/capture/*\": allow\n218:   edit:\n219:     \"*\": deny\n220:     \"src/azure_kinect_comfyui/capture/**\": allow\n221:     \"tests/capture/**\": allow\n222:     \"fixtures/**\": allow\n223: ---\n224: \n225: You own only mocked/replay capture code. Do not import or install Azure Kinect SDKs.\n226: Implement against synthetic fixtures and the project contracts. Never access hardware.\n227: EOF\n228: \n229: cat > .opencode/agents/pose-worker.md <<'EOF'\n230: ---\n231: description: Builds Kinect skeleton remap and pose-map rendering against fixtures\n232: mode: subagent\n233: hidden: true\n234: temperature: 0.2\n235: maxSteps: 22\n236: permission:\n237:   external_directory: deny\n238:   task: deny\n239:   webfetch: ask\n240:   websearch: ask\n241:   bash:\n242:     \"*\": deny\n243:     \"git status*\": allow\n244:     \"git diff*\": allow\n245:     \"git add src/azure_kinect_comfyui/pose/* tests/pose/* fixtures/*\": allow\n246:     \"git commit -m *\": ask\n247:     \"python -m pytest tests/pose/*\": allow\n248:   edit:\n249:     \"*\": deny\n250:     \"src/azure_kinect_comfyui/pose/**\": allow\n251:     \"tests/pose/**\": allow\n252:     \"fixtures/**\": allow\n253: ---\n254: \n255: You own only skeleton mapping and deterministic pose rendering. Do not modify capture,\n256: ComfyUI, FLUX, shared contracts, or project configuration. Treat ambiguous mappings\n257: as BLOCKED_INTERFACE_CHANGE requests rather than guessing.\n258: EOF\n259: \n260: cat > .opencode/agents/comfy-worker.md <<'EOF'\n261: ---\n262: description: Builds ComfyUI node scaffolding using mock-file input only\n263: mode: subagent\n264: hidden: true\n265: temperature: 0.2\n266: maxSteps: 20\n267: permission:\n268:   external_directory: deny\n269:   task: deny\n270:   webfetch: ask\n271:   websearch: ask\n272:   bash:\n273:     \"*\": deny\n274:     \"git status*\": allow\n275:     \"git diff*\": allow\n276:     \"git add src/azure_kinect_comfyui/comfy/* tests/comfy/*\": allow\n277:     \"git commit -m *\": ask\n278:     \"python -m pytest tests/comfy/*\": allow\n279:   edit:\n280:     \"*\": deny\n281:     \"src/azure_kinect_comfyui/comfy/**\": allow\n282:     \"tests/comfy/**\": allow\n283: ---\n284: \n285: You own only mock-backed ComfyUI node scaffolding. Do not write into an installed\n286: ComfyUI directory, download models, or change FLUX/Klein workflow behavior.\n287: EOF\n288: \n289: cat > .opencode/agents/reviewer.md <<'EOF'\n290: ---\n291: description: Read-only verifier for task contracts, diffs, and test evidence\n292: mode: subagent\n293: hidden: true\n294: temperature: 0.1\n295: maxSteps: 12\n296: permission:\n297:   read: allow\n298:   glob: allow\n299:   grep: allow\n300:   list: allow\n301:   edit: deny\n302:   external_directory: deny\n303:   task: deny\n304:   webfetch: ask\n305:   websearch: ask\n306:   bash:\n307:     \"*\": deny\n308:     \"git status*\": allow\n309:     \"git diff*\": allow\n310:     \"git show*\": allow\n311:     \"python -m pytest tests/*\": allow\n312: ---\n313: \n314: You are an independent reviewer. Never modify files or approve your own work.\n315: Verify path ownership, test evidence, contract compliance, and unsupported claims.\n316: Return PASS, FAIL, or NEEDS_HUMAN_DECISION with concise evidence.\n317: EOF\n318: \n319: cat > contracts/task.schema.json <<'EOF'\n320: {\n321:   \"$schema\": \"https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema\",\n322:   \"title\": \"Agent Task Contract\",\n323:   \"type\": \"object\",\n324:   \"required\": [\n325:     \"task_id\", \"owner\", \"objective\", \"owned_paths\",\n326:     \"acceptance_criteria\", \"allowed_tests\", \"max_attempts\"\n327:   ],\n328:   \"properties\": {\n329:     \"task_id\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"pattern\": \"^[A-Z]+-[0-9]{3}$\" },\n330:     \"owner\": {\n331:       \"type\": \"string\",\n332:       \"enum\": [\"capture-worker\", \"pose-worker\", \"comfy-worker\", \"reviewer\"]\n333:     },\n334:     \"objective\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 20 },\n335:     \"owned_paths\": { \"type\": \"array\", \"minItems\": 1, \"items\": { \"type\": \"string\" } },\n336:     \"read_only_paths\": { \"type\": \"array\", \"items\": { \"type\": \"string\" } },\n337:     \"forbidden_paths\": { \"type\": \"array\", \"items\": { \"type\": \"string\" } },\n338:     \"acceptance_criteria\": { \"type\": \"array\", \"minItems\": 1, \"items\": { \"type\": \"string\" } },\n339:     \"allowed_tests\": { \"type\": \"array\", \"items\": { \"type\": \"string\" } },\n340:     \"max_attempts\": { \"type\": \"integer\", \"minimum\": 1, \"maximum\": 2 },\n341:     \"requires_human_approval\": { \"type\": \"boolean\", \"default\": false }\n342:   },\n343:   \"additionalProperties\": false\n344: }\n345: EOF\n346: \n347: cat > contracts/status.schema.json <<'EOF'\n348: {\n349:   \"$schema\": \"https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema\",\n350:   \"title\": \"Worker Status Contract\",\n351:   \"type\": \"object\",\n352:   \"required\": [\n353:     \"task_id\", \"status\", \"summary\", \"files_changed\",\n354:     \"tests\", \"commit\", \"risks\", \"next_action\"\n355:   ],\n356:   \"properties\": {\n357:     \"task_id\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n358:     \"status\": {\n359:       \"type\": \"string\",\n360:       \"enum\": [\"completed\", \"blocked\", \"needs_approval\", \"failed\"]\n361:     },\n362:     \"summary\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n363:     \"files_changed\": { \"type\": \"array\", \"items\": { \"type\": \"string\" } },\n364:     \"tests\": { \"type\": \"array\", \"items\": { \"type\": \"object\" } },\n365:     \"commit\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n366:     \"risks\": { \"type\": \"array\", \"items\": { \"type\": \"string\" } },\n367:     \"next_action\": { \"type\": \"string\" }\n368:   },\n369:   \"additionalProperties\": false\n370: }\n371: EOF\n372: \n373: cat > docs/PHASE0.md <<'EOF'\n374: # Phase 0: Hardware-independent foundation\n375: \n376: ## In scope\n377: - Agent orchestration safety harness\n378: - Synthetic KinectFrame fixtures\n379: - Mock/replay frame source\n380: - Skeleton remapping and pose rendering\n381: - Mock-backed ComfyUI custom-node package scaffolding\n382: - Unit tests and contract tests\n383: \n384: ## 